President Donald Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of Florida due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding is now available for crisis counseling and emergency protective measures in all areas of Florida affected by COVID-19. Gracia B. Szczech has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made in the future based on assessments and requests from the state. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.